name: 🏴Yon🏴 @ 🌕6.0 Spoilers 🌕
description: 🏳️‍🌈| any pronouns | 2D Art Generalist/Comic Artist | 4cm tall frog | 4threset@gmail.com ¦ ADHD+Autistic | Author of Chinatop | Rep'd by @TakahashiPerry
tweet:
Another thing is when I eat dishes with rice, I have to eat all of them in order.
1. Equal amount of rice on my spoon with meat.
2. Rice with vegetables
3. Rice with the third dish

And repeat until I finish eating. If I lose track of that I get frustrated which happens often LOL

tweet:
@ShyGodot I do know that sentence structure is different for ASL, if you're including information on Time, then usually the sign for Time comes first! Like :

"I'm going to the store at 3 pm"

3 - EVENING(pm) - I - STORE.

A lot of adjectives and grammar is shortened in ASL!

description: 🏳️‍🌈| any pronouns | 2D Art Generalist/Comic Artist | 4cm tall frog | 4threset@gmail.com ¦ ADHD+Autistic | Author of Chinatop | Rep'd by @TakahashiPerry
tweet: And usually in games and media you *know * when the writer *knows* this too. Like how characters may push through sickness to work, in the environments they design etc I suppose! When things are literally held together by duct tape.

name: 🏴Yon🏴 @ 🌕6.0 Spoilers 🌕
description: 🏳️‍🌈| any pronouns | 2D Art Generalist/Comic Artist | 4cm tall frog | 4threset@gmail.com ¦ ADHD+Autistic | Author of Chinatop | Rep'd by @TakahashiPerry
tweet: Impulse buying, buying cheap solutions that cost more in the long term. Poverty sometimes isn't having enough food but also just barely scraping by and realising 8 months down the line you've been in survival mode fot years?

name: 🏴Yon🏴 @ 🌕6.0 Spoilers 🌕
description: 🏳️‍🌈| any pronouns | 2D Art Generalist/Comic Artist | 4cm tall frog | 4threset@gmail.com ¦ ADHD+Autistic | Author of Chinatop | Rep'd by @TakahashiPerry
tweet:
That said, it's made me think a lot about how poverty and trauma manifests differently in ways we don't think about or isn't usually portrayed in media. 
Like food hoarding, refusing to buy food even with the funds and the need to be a hyper-pleaser.

name: 🏴Yon🏴 @ 🌕6.0 Spoilers 🌕
description: 🏳️‍🌈| any pronouns | 2D Art Generalist/Comic Artist | 4cm tall frog | 4threset@gmail.com ¦ ADHD+Autistic | Author of Chinatop | Rep'd by @TakahashiPerry
tweet:
For a long time I always felt guilty for not wanting to eat leftover food and wanting to buy food instead? Because its wasteful and Im being picky.

But I think I've recently come to the acceptance that it's not a bad thing to want fresh food.

name: 🏴Yon🏴 @ 🌕6.0 Spoilers 🌕
description: 🏳️‍🌈| any pronouns | 2D Art Generalist/Comic Artist | 4cm tall frog | 4threset@gmail.com ¦ ADHD+Autistic | Author of Chinatop | Rep'd by @TakahashiPerry
tweet: I recently learnt that food hoarding is a symptom of PTSD from not having enough food in the past. The fridge in my home is usually overstocked but it's mostly leftover food from previous days etc. So a lot of fresh food sometimes goes bad because of it.
